                                    <h4>Information Classification</h4>
                                    
                                    <p>The following statement was discussed and approved with the Cirrus Steering Committee on 27-Feb-2015, and was approved for communication. The Steering Committee consisted of: Mike Meadows, John VandeWiele, Jen Oleksiew, Sue Gale, Rich Gargas, Chris Reed, Rich Grogut. This statement is considered effective, and will be reviewed and revised over time.</p>

                                    <p>The Force.com platform that Cirrus provides has sufficiently developed the Global Services Org (GSO) Architecture to <strong>accept orange CCI</strong> and with proper risk discussions <strong>can also accept Red CCI</strong>. We already have application use cases that consume, store and transform information that has been classified as red CCI in production. We are not however ready to open this up without any guidance or controls, and these uses cases were approved because the appropriate risk assessment and controls were put in place.</p>
                                     
                                    <p><strong>However, it is very important that every use case with information classified as red, have the appropriate risk mitigation conversation to ensure the specific use case and scenario is acceptable, and appropriate controls are put in place.</strong></p>
                                     
                                    <p>Currently, the Cirrus Steering Committee is the governing body that needs to be informed of the use case, and to validate that the appropriate risk mitigations are in place. Before coming to the Cirrus Steering Committee you should also engage your area’s Information Security Liaison to help prepare for the discussion.</p>

                                    <p>It is also important to note, that as the Information Classification framework is in continuous evolution as it matures, Cirrus will continue to partner and make further recommendations that will be implemented by our Force.com Security Roadmap. This will include integration into myAccess @ Lilly, advanced testing, security monitoring and potentially encryption services.</p>
                                     
                                    <p>For questions, please contact<apex:outputLink value="{! $Page.LAPD_CirrusTeam}"> Chris Reed</apex:outputLink> our Security Liason for force.com by Cirrus, or<apex:outputLink value="{! $Page.LAPD_CirrusTeam}"> Richard Grogut</apex:outputLink>.</p>
                                    
                                    <h4>GxP</h4>

                                    <p>The Cirrus platforms (GSO1, GSO2) and methodology have not yet been sufficiently developed to support the requirements of highly regulated applications, such as those impacting Current Good Manufacturing Practice (cGMP) or critical applications impacting Good Clinical Practice (GCP). GCP will require some discussion prior completely excluding this and this can be done in collaboration with Quality.</p>

                                    <p>Cirrus processes and support tools have been assessed by Computer Systems Quality Assurance (CSQA) and have been determined to be sufficient to support existing uses for Good Promotional Practices (GPP) and Lilly Quality Critical Systems.</p>

                                    <p>Cirrus is not in a position to support highly regulated GMP or GCP (excluding certain cases) applications  at this point in time.  As a part of the Global Customer Support Program, the Cirrus team will continue to develop processes and controls to allow it to support highly regulated applications later in 2015.</p>

                                    <p>No Apps targeting the existing Cirrus platforms (GSO1, GSO2) should plan to initiate development work on GMP or critical GCP projects until a second Self Inspection, planned for late 2015, has been completed and shows that the requirements for such systems can be supported.</p>

                                    <p>If you have any questions or concerns, please reach out to your quality representative or<apex:outputLink value="{! $Page.LAPD_CirrusTeam}"> Stuart Gittings</apex:outputLink>.</p>
